      "text": "Now I can see the structure. There's:\n- `spx-pre-ak` (small \"AK\" at top)\n- `spx-pre-line` (divider)\n- `spx-pre-word` (\"PRESENTS\" typewriter)\n- `spx-ak` (the BIG AK that comes after)\n\nThe overlap is happening because:\n- The `spx-pre-ak` (small AK) fades out at 2.8s\n- The `spx-ak` (big AK) starts at 3.0s — only 0.2s gap, plus both are absolutely positioned in the center, so they overlap as one fades and the other scales in\n\nThe user wants:\n- ONE big AK (just `spx-ak`)\n- \"PRESENTS\" as the typewriter directly under it (instead of `spx-pre-word` in a separate `spx-presents` wrapper)\n\nThe cleanest fix:\n1. Remove the `#spx-presents` wrapper and `#spx-pre-ak` and `#spx-pre-line` from the HTML\n2. Move `#spx-pre-word` (the \"PRESENTS\" typewriter) into the main splash container alongside the big `#spx-ak`\n3. Place the typewriter right under the big AK, not absolutely\n4. Adjust timing so PRESENTS types in just after the big AK appears\n\nOr even simpler — keep `spx-presents` as just a container for the \"PRESENTS\" text below the big AK, and delete `spx-pre-ak` and `spx-pre-line` entirely. Or simplest: drop the small \"AK\" and the line, keep the big AK and the \"PRESENTS\" typewriter.\n\nLet me think about the best approach:\n\nThe cleanest restructure:\n- Delete `#spx-pre-ak` (small AK) and `#spx-pre-line` (divider)\n- Move `#spx-pre-word` (\"PRESENTS\") to be a sibling of `#spx-ak` inside a `#spx-presents` wrapper, OR just leave it standalone\n- Reposition so PRESENTS is just below the big AK\n- Time it so: big AK appears → PRESENTS types underneath\n\nActually, looking at the code, `#spx-pre-word` is already positioned by the parent's flex layout (`#spx-presents` is a flex column). If I:\n1. Remove `#spx-pre-ak` and `#spx-pre-line`\n2. Add a wrapper that contains both `#spx-ak` and `#spx-pre-word`\n\nOr simpler still: just delete the small AK and the line, and use the existing `#spx-presents` wrapper which now only contains the big AK + the \"PRESENTS\" typewriter. Move `#spx-ak` inside `#spx-presents` so they're in the same flex container.\n\nWait, `#spx-ak` is absolutely positioned according to the CSS at line 214. Let me check that CSS more carefully.\n\nLet me read the relevant CSS sections.",
