    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "OK so the big `#spx-ak` is at the center, absolutely positioned, and it pulses/scales for 3.1s starting at 3.0s. The user wants:\n\n**Final intent:** One big AK. \"PRESENTS\" typewriter directly under it.\n\nThe current `spx-presents` wrapper has `spx-pre-ak` (small AK), `spx-pre-line` (divider), and `spx-pre-word` (PRESENTS typewriter). And it overlaps with the big `#spx-ak` because the big one is absolutely positioned on top of the wrapper.\n\n**Cleanest fix:** \n1. Remove `#spx-pre-ak` (small AK) — gone\n2. Remove `#spx-pre-line` (divider) — gone  \n3. Restructure: make `#spx-ak` (big AK) part of `#spx-presents` flex column, with `#spx-pre-word` (PRESENTS) directly below it\n4. Remove `position: absolute` from `#spx-ak` so the flex layout works\n5. Or simpler: drop the wrapper entirely, just stack the big AK and the PRESENTS typewriter\n\nActually, even simpler — let's keep the flex column wrapper but stack them. The big AK doesn't need to be position:absolute when it's inside the centered splash. The `spx` parent is already `display: flex; align-items: center; justify-content: center;`.\n\nPlan:\n- HTML: \n  ```\n  <div id=\"spx-presents\">\n    <div id=\"spx-ak\">AK</div>  <!-- big AK -->\n    <div id=\"spx-pre-word\">PRESENTS</div>  <!-- typewriter underneath -->\n  </div>\n  ```\n- Remove the small `#spx-pre-ak` and the `#spx-pre-line` divs\n- CSS: change `#spx-ak` to not be `position: absolute`, and adjust its size\n\nWait — but `#spx-ak` also has the big spxAK animation (3.1s) that includes fading out. If I keep that animation, the big AK will still fade out, but I want it to STAY for the rest of the splash. Hmm.\n\nLet me re-read the user's message: \"still overlapping when i was hoping it to be just below the AK and there to be just one ak only but a presents beneath would be a perfect touch\"\n\nSo:\n- One big AK (not two)\n- \"PRESENTS\" beneath it (typewriter)\n- The overlap is the small AK + big AK stacking on top of each other\n\nThe current animation timeline:\n- 0s: page loads\n- 0-2.8s: small AK + line + PRESENTS typewriter plays, then spx-presents fades out\n- 3.0-6.1s: big AK pulses and fades out\n- 5.6-8.0s: logo fades in\n- 6.5-7.7s: tagline fades in\n\nThe user wants:\n- ONE big AK that appears\n- \"PRESENTS\" types out directly below it\n- Then the rest of the splash (logo, tagline) takes over\n\nSo the new timeline should be:\n- 0s: page loads\n- 0-?: big AK appears\n- Just after: \"PRESENTS\" types out below it\n- 3-4s: big AK + PRESENTS fade out together\n- Then logo, tagline, exit\n\nOr, more cinematic: \n- 0-0.6s: big AK scales in\n- 0.6-1.3s: PRESENTS types under it\n- 1.3-3.0s: hold for a beat\n- 3.0-3.6s: fade out together\n- 3.6s: radial pulse, logo starts to appear, etc.\n\nLet me design this. I'll:\n1. Delete `#spx-pre-ak` and `#spx-pre-line` from HTML\n2. Make `#spx-ak` (big AK) sit inside `#spx-presents` flex column with `#spx-pre-word` (PRESENTS typewriter) below it\n3. Make `#spx-ak` non-absolute and have a different animation (appear, hold, fade)\n4. Update the `spxPresFade` to keep both elements visible together\n5. Shift the rest of the splash timeline earlier (since we're not waiting 2.8s for \"AK presents\" intro)\n\nActually, you know what — let's keep the existing splash structure but just simplify what's inside `#spx-presents`. The big AK can just be inside it.\n\nLet me design the new CSS:\n\n```css\n#spx-presents {\n  position: absolute;\n  display: flex;\n  flex-direction: column;\n  align-items: center;\n  gap: 24px;\n  opacity: 0;\n  animation: spxPresFade 3.0s cubic-bezier(0.4,0,0.2,1) forwards;\n}\n#spx-ak {  /* big AK - no longer absolute */\n  font-family: 'Exo 2', sans-serif; font-weight: 900;\n  font-size: clamp(120px, 28vmin, 300px);\n  line-height: 1; letter-spacing: -0.03em; color: #39FF14;\n  text-shadow:\n    0 0 24px #39FF14,\n    0 0 70px rgba(57,255,20,0.65),\n    0 0 140px rgba(57,255,20,0.38),\n    0 0 260px rgba(57,255,20,0.18);\n  animation: spxAKIn 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.2, 1) 0.2s both;\n}\n#spx-pre-word {  /* PRESENTS typewriter */\n  font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace; font-weight: 500;\n  font-size: clamp(12px, 2.2vw, 16px);\n  letter-spacing: 0.55em; text-transform: uppercase;\n  color: #C8C8C8;\n  overflow: hidden; white-space: nowrap;\n  width: 0;\n  border-right: 2px solid #39FF14;\n  box-sizing: content-box;\n  animation:\n    spxType 0.8s steps(8,end) 0.95s both,\n    spxCursor 0.6s step-end 0.95s 3,\n    spxCursorOff 0s 2.95s both;\n}\n@keyframes spxPresFade {\n  0%    { opacity: 0; }\n  10%   { opacity: 1; }\n  75%   { opacity: 1; }\n  100%  { opacity: 0; }\n}\n@keyframes spxAKIn {\n  from { opacity: 0; transform: scale(0.7) translateY(20px); }\n  to   { opacity: 1; transform: scale(1) translateY(0); }\n}\n```\n\nAnd the new timeline:\n- 0.2-0.8s: big AK appears\n- 0.95-1.75s: PRESENTS types underneath\n- 1.75-3.0s: hold\n- 3.0-3.2s: PRESENTS + AK fade out together\n- 3.2s: radial pulse\n- 3.5s: logo starts to fade in\n- 4.5s: tagline starts to fade in\n- 5.5s: exit splash (around 5.8s)\n\nLet me actually keep the original spxAK animation feel (the pulse) but adapt it to a single big AK:\n\nWait, simpler: just use the existing spxAK animation (which pulses and fades out) but trim it. The big AK pulses from 3.0s for 3.1s, fading out at the end. If I move it earlier, say starting at 0.2s and finishing at 3.0s (fade out at 88% of 3.1s = 2.7s + 0.2s = 2.9s), then the rest of the splash kicks in at 3.0s.\n\nActually let me just write this clean. I'll:\n1. Remove `spx-pre-ak` and `spx-pre-line` from HTML\n2. Move `spx-ak` inside `spx-presents` (or just make it a flex sibling with spx-pre-word)\n3. Adjust CSS so big AK is in flow (not absolute), uses spxAKIn for entry, fades out with parent\n4. Update timing in JS\n\nLet me also think about whether to have the big AK pulse at all, or just appear and fade out with the wrapper. The current spxAK has a nice pulse-then-fade-out. Let me keep a simpler version: appear → hold → fade out (with the wrapper).\n\nLet me write the patch.\n\nKey changes:\n\n**HTML (lines 301-308):**\n```html\n<!-- before -->\n<div id=\"spx-presents\">\n  <div id=\"spx-pre-ak\">AK</div>\n  <div id=\"spx-pre-line\"></div>\n  <div id=\"spx-pre-word\">PRESENTS</div>\n</div>\n<div id=\"spx-ak\">AK</div>\n```\n```html\n<!-- after -->\n<div id=\"spx-presents\">\n  <div id=\"spx-ak\">AK</div>\n  <div id=\"spx-pre-word\">PRESENTS</div>\n</div>\n```\n\n**CSS:**\n- Remove `#spx-pre-ak` and `#spx-pre-line` rules and keyframes\n- Update `#spx-ak` to be relative, not absolute, with a new animation `spxAKIn`\n- Update `#spx-presents` to use new timings\n- Update `#spx-pre-word` to start at 0.95s\n\n**JS:** shift the rest of the timeline to start ~3.0s after splash begin:\n- spxRadialPulse: 3.5s → 3.0s (after presents fades out at 3.0s)\n- spxLogo: 5.6s → 3.5s\n- spxTagline: 6.5s → 4.5s\n- JS exit: 7800ms → 5800ms\n- JS remove: 8750ms → 6800ms\n\nHmm, but the radial pulse is on `#spx-radial`, and the logo is positioned absolutely. They appear after the presents wrapper has faded. Let me think about the visual flow.\n\nActually, let me re-read what's in the original splash. The user said it's still overlapping. So the issue is the small AK + big AK overlap. After the small one fades (at 2.8s) the big one starts (at 3.0s) — but only 0.2s gap means they overlap visually if the fade isn't fully done.\n\nThe simplest fix: just remove the small AK and the line. Keep the big AK. Move the \"PRESENTS\" typewriter below the big AK. Make the rest of the splash start after the wrapper fades.\n\nLet me write this out. I'll also make the splash shorter total since the user has been patient with the long intro.\n\nNew timeline:\n- 0.0-0.2s: page loads\n- 0.2-0.8s: big AK scales in\n- 0.95-1.75s: PRESENTS types under it\n- 1.75-3.0s: hold\n- 3.0-3.2s: wrapper fades out\n- 3.2s: radial pulse starts (2 cycles)\n- 3.5s: logo starts to fade in\n- 4.5s: tagline starts to fade in\n- 5.5s: splash exit starts\n- 5.5s + 250ms: splash DOM removed\n\nWait, I should match the existing JS exit pattern. Let me check what the JS does.",
