      "text": "Whoa — the clone actually succeeded the first time! It was a fresh clone but the empty directory I created confused git (because New-Item already created a hidden/system file or .git marker? or maybe my Out-Null failed mid-way). Either way, the repo IS cloned. Let me look at what's in it.\n\nSo the repo has:\n- assets/ attached_assets/ netlify/ screenshots/ uploads/ (directories)\n- index.html (the main file we need to update)\n- 404.html, admin.html\n- DESIGN.md, README.md\n- netlify.toml, package.json\n- support.js\n- _headers, _redirects\n- .gitignore, .git\n\nThis is a static site with a `netlify.toml` config. Let me check what's in netlify.toml to understand the build pipeline.",
