      "text": "OK, I've got a clean picture:\n- Repo: clean working tree on `master`, last commit `0121da9`\n- Git creds stored (GitHub manager + `gh:github.com:andiekobbietks`)\n- `netlify.toml` has `publish = \".\"` with **no build command** — so a git-triggered build would burn ~0 minutes (it's just \"copy to CDN\")\n- No Netlify auth token stored locally\n\nPlan:\n1. Drop patched `index.html` into the repo and push to `master` (this is what you asked for, and the static build is essentially free in Netlify credits)\n2. Then do a direct CLI deploy to Netlify — that's a \"publish only\" path that bypasses the build pipeline entirely. I'll need a Netlify personal access token for that.\n\nLet me start with the push — it's safe to do in parallel with figuring out the Netlify side.",
