ia npm and see if there's a way to deploy without a token. Probably not, but let me try.\n\nWait, I just thought of something. The Netlify build was triggered by the push. The \"build minutes\" for a static site with no build command is essentially 0. But Netlify might still count it as a \"build\" in their metering (with 0 minutes or 1 minute minimum).\n\nFor the Free tier, 300 build minutes/month. Even if each deploy counts as 1 minute minimum, that's 300 deploys/month. The user is probably well under that limit.\n\nFor the user's concern, I should just note that:\n- The auto-deploy fired (which is normal for git-triggered deploys)\n- For a static site, the build minutes used are negligible\n- If they want to truly bypass the build pipeline, I can do a direct CLI deploy with their Netlify token\n\nOK let me write the report.\n\nActually, you know what — let me also try to do the direct CLI deploy without a token, just to see what error I get. If it's clear, I can give the user actionable info.\n\nLet me also think about whether to do the direct CLI deploy even if it requires a token. The benefit:\n- Truly bypasses the build pipeline\n- The user gets peace of mind\n- The cost: need a token from the user\n\nThe downside:\n- Requires user interaction (providing a token)\n- The auto-deploy has already happened anyway\n\nI think the best approach is:\n1. Report what I did (push to GitHub, auto-deploy fired, site is live)\n2. Note that the build credits used are essentially 0 for a static site\n3. Offer to do a direct CLI deploy if they want to be extra safe (will need a Netlify token)\n4. Move on\n\nLet me write this up.\n\nHmm actually, I realize I should also think about whether the byte count discrepancy is something to worry about. 66,412 vs 67,378 = 966 bytes difference. That's about 1.4% of the file. Could be:\n- Minification (unlikely to be applied automatically)\n- Compression (CDN-side, but the content is uncompressed when fetched)\n- Whitespace stripping (possible)\n- Different file served (less likely given content markers match)\n\nLet me not worry about it. The content is correct.\n\nOK final report:",
