    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I see what's going on:\n\n- `.card::before` creates the green L-shape (top + left border) in the top-left corner, 38px × 38px\n- On hover, it grows to 80px × 80px — which is the \"small point\" the user is complaining about. It grows but stays in the corner.\n\nThe user wants it to expand to cover the ENTIRE element on hover, with a slight overshoot (genesis/magnifier effect).\n\nThe challenge: the current `::before` only has top and left borders. To trace the full card perimeter, I'd need all 4 sides. The cleanest way is to use 4 separate elements/positions or a single element with a wide box-shadow.\n\nLet me think about the best approach. There are a few ways:\n\n**Option 1: Use `::before` with all 4 sides on hover (via box-shadow or border tricks)**\n- `::before` can only have one set of borders. If I add bottom and right borders, they'd be on the top and left in the natural orientation. I can use a large box-shadow on a transparent border to \"fake\" the right and bottom.\n\n**Option 2: Use `::before` + `::after` (one for top-left, one for bottom-right)**\n- `::before` is the existing top-left L\n- `::after` would be the bottom-right L\n- On hover, both expand to cover the full border\n\n**Option 3: Use a single element with a wide box-shadow that traces the whole border**\n- The corner element can be a 2px tall/wide line that grows to wrap the entire card\n\nI think the cleanest is **Option 2** with `::after` for the bottom-right corner. The hover would animate both corners to expand. But \"expand to cover the entire space\" means tracing the full perimeter, not just two corners.\n\nLet me think again. The user wants:\n- On hover, the green corner marker expands to cover the entire card border\n- With a slight overshoot/expansion feel (magnifier effect)\n- Like a \"genesis\" reveal\n\nThe most elegant approach: use a single `::before` element that animates to a full border. We can:\n- Keep the `::before` for the top-left corner (default state)\n- On hover, animate the `::before` to be a full border around the card (using box-shadow or by changing border-color/width on all sides)\n\nActually, the cleanest way: use a `::before` with a `border` that has different colored edges:\n- Default: only top and left borders are green\n- On hover: all 4 borders are green\n\nBut CSS `border` doesn't easily support per-side colors with animation. We'd need border-color: rgba(0,0,0,0) on bottom/right at rest, then animate them to green.\n\nActually, the issue is that `::before` is positioned with `top: -1px; left: -1px; width: 38px; height: 38px`. So it's a 38x38 box in the corner. To make it cover the full card, we need to expand it.\n\nPlan:\n- Default: 38x38 in top-left corner with top+left green borders\n- Hover: 100% width/height with all 4 borders green + slight overshoot\n\nLet me write the new CSS:\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: -1px; left: -1px;\n  width: 38px; height: 38px;\n  border: 2px solid transparent;\n  border-top-color: #39FF14;\n  border-left-color: #39FF14;\n  border-top-left-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow: 0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55);\n  transition:\n    width 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.4, 0.64, 1),\n    height 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.34, 1.4, 0.64, 1) 0.05s,\n    border-color 0.3s ease 0.15s,\n    box-shadow 0.4s ease,\n    transform 0.4s ease;\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n.card:hover::before {\n  width: calc(100% + 2px);\n  height: calc(100% + 2px);\n  border-top-color: #39FF14;\n  border-right-color: #39FF14;\n  border-bottom-color: #39FF14;\n  border-left-color: #39FF14;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  transform: scale(1.015); /* slight overshoot for magnifier feel */\n  box-shadow:\n    0 0 8px #39FF14,\n    0 0 24px rgba(57,255,20,0.5),\n    0 0 48px rgba(57,255,20,0.25);\n}\n```\n\nWait, there's a problem. The `::before` has `top: -1px; left: -1px` so it's offset to align with the card's border. When we make it 100% wide/tall, we need to account for that offset.\n\nLet me think:\n- The card is at, say, 300x200px with border-radius 8px\n- The card has `border: 1px solid #242424` \n- The `::before` is at `top: -1px; left: -1px` with width 38px height 38px\n- The `::before` has `border-top: 2px solid #39FF14; border-left: 2px solid #39FF14;`\n- This places the green L on the outside of the card (overlapping the card's border)\n\nFor the hover, if I make the `::before` 100% wide/tall:\n- The 2px green border would be 2px outside the card (because of top: -1px, left: -1px)\n- This creates a \"double border\" effect with the card's own 1px border\n\nThat's actually a nice effect — the green border appears slightly outside the card, like a glow frame.\n\nTo make the `::before` cover the full card INCLUDING its border area, I need to set:\n- `top: -1px; left: -1px` (already)\n- `width: calc(100% + 2px); height: calc(100% + 2px)` (extend 2px past the right and bottom)\n- And the borders need to be on all sides\n\nWait actually, with `box-sizing: content-box` (default), `width: 100%` means content width only, not including border or padding. The `::before` doesn't have padding, so width: 100% = 100% of parent's content width. But the parent is the card which has its own border, padding, and width: auto.\n\nHmm, this is getting complex. Let me simplify by setting `box-sizing: border-box` and using `inset: 0` or similar.\n\nActually, a cleaner approach: position the `::before` to cover the entire card on hover:\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: -1px;  /* same as top/right/bottom/left: -1px */\n  width: 38px;\n  height: 38px;\n  border: 2px solid transparent;\n  border-top-color: #39FF14;\n  border-left-color: #39FF14;\n  border-top-left-radius: 8px;\n  ...\n  transition: all 0.4s ...;\n}\n.card:hover::before {\n  width: 100%;\n  height: 100%;\n  border-color: #39FF14;  /* all 4 sides */\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  transform: scale(1.015);\n}\n```\n\nWait, `inset: -1px` would set top/right/bottom/left to -1px, but the width/height would be the actual size. If width is 38px, the element occupies from -1px to 37px (relative to the parent). When width becomes 100%, the element occupies from -1px to (parentWidth - 1px) — extending 1px past the right edge.\n\nThis is getting complex. Let me simplify by using `top: -1px; left: -1px; right: ?; bottom: ?;` and then animating `right: 0; bottom: 0` on hover.\n\nActually, the simplest approach:\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: -1px;\n  left: -1px;\n  width: 38px;\n  height: 38px;\n  border: 2px solid transparent;\n  border-top-color: #39FF14;\n  border-left-color: #39FF14;\n  border-top-left-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow: 0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55);\n  transition:\n    width 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),\n    height 0.45s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) 0.05s,\n    border-color 0.3s ease 0.2s,\n    box-shadow 0.4s ease,\n    border-radius 0.4s ease;\n  pointer-events: none;\n}\n.card:hover::before {\n  width: calc(100% + 2px);\n  height: calc(100% + 2px);\n  border-color: #39FF14;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow:\n    0 0 10px #39FF14,\n    0 0 28px rgba(57,255,20,0.5),\n    0 0 56px rgba(57,255,20,0.25);\n}\n```\n\nThis should:\n- Start as a 38x38 corner with top+left green borders\n- On hover: expand to 100%+2px width/height (covering the whole card), all 4 borders become green, box-shadow glows\n\nThe slight overshoot for the \"magnifier\" feel — I could add a `transform: scale(1.015)` but the card itself doesn't transform, so a scale on `::before` would extend it past the card edges. Let me try without scale first.\n\nActually, the user said \"expand on a bit not just to a point\" — they want it to extend a bit beyond the card edges. The `+2px` does that, but a `scale(1.01)` would also work. Let me use scale for the magnifier feel.\n\nHmm wait, I need to think about the box-shadow. With `transform: scale(1.015)`, the box-shadow also scales, which might not look good (the glow becomes bigger and softer).\n\nLet me try a different approach: use a tiny scale + larger box-shadow, and the card itself can have a subtle transform too.\n\nActually, let me just make the ::before expand to cover the card, with a slight overshoot via a small `transform: scale()`. The transition timing function can have a slight overshoot (cubic-bezier with a bouncy end) for the \"genesis\" feel.\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: -1px;\n  left: -1px;\n  width: 38px;\n  height: 38px;\n  border: 2px solid transparent;\n  border-top-color: #39FF14;\n  border-left-color: #39FF14;\n  border-top-left-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow: 0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55);\n  transition:\n    width 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),\n    height 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) 0.05s,\n    border-color 0.35s ease 0.2s,\n    box-shadow 0.4s ease 0.1s,\n    transform 0.4s ease 0.1s;\n  pointer-events: none;\n  z-index: 1;\n}\n.card:hover::before {\n  width: calc(100% + 4px);\n  height: calc(100% + 4px);\n  border-color: #39FF14;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  transform: translate(-2px, -2px); /* counteract the extra 2px on each side */\n  box-shadow:\n    0 0 10px #39FF14,\n    0 0 28px rgba(57,255,20,0.5),\n    0 0 56px rgba(57,255,20,0.25);\n}\n```\n\nWait this is getting complex. Let me simplify.\n\nThe card has its own border-radius: 8px. The `::before` is positioned at top: -1px, left: -1px with width 38px, height 38px. To cover the full card, I need to extend the `::before` to:\n- left: -1px (stay)\n- right: -1px (extend to the right edge of the card minus 1px)\n- top: -1px (stay)\n- bottom: -1px (extend to the bottom edge of the card minus 1px)\n\nThe easiest way: use `inset: -1px` (which sets all four) and have width/height at default (auto), but then we need explicit width/height. Let me use:\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  inset: -1px;  /* top/right/bottom/left all set to -1px */\n  width: 38px;\n  height: 38px;\n  ...\n}\n```\n\nWait, with `inset: -1px` AND `width: 38px`, the `width` takes precedence (the element is 38px wide, positioned with left: -1px, so it extends from -1px to 37px). The `right: -1px` is ignored when width is explicit.\n\nFor the hover state, I need the `::before` to extend to the right and bottom of the card. The cleanest way:\n- Set `width: auto; height: auto; right: -1px; bottom: -1px;` on hover\n- OR set `width: calc(100% + 2px); height: calc(100% + 2px);` on hover (with `right: auto; bottom: auto;`)\n\nLet me use the calc approach:\n\n```css\n.card::before {\n  content: '';\n  position: absolute;\n  top: -1px;\n  left: -1px;\n  width: 38px;\n  height: 38px;\n  ...\n  transition:\n    width 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1),\n    height 0.5s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1) 0.05s,\n    border-color 0.35s ease 0.2s,\n    box-shadow 0.4s ease 0.1s;\n  pointer-events: none;\n  z-index: 1;\n}\n.card:hover::before {\n  width: calc(100% + 2px);\n  height: calc(100% + 2px);\n  border-color: #39FF14;\n  border-radius: 8px;\n  box-shadow:\n    0 0 10px #39FF14,\n    0 0 28px rgba(57,255,20,0.5),\n    0 0 56px rgba(57,255,20,0.25);\n}\n```\n\nThis should work. The `::before` starts as a 38x38 corner with top+left borders. On hover, it expands to 100%+2px (extending 1px past the right and bottom edges) with all 4 borders green.\n\nFor the \"magnifier\" feel, I can add a slight scale on the card itself:\n```css\n.card { transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s, transform 0.4s cubic-bezier(0.22, 1, 0.36, 1); }\n.card:hover { \n  transform: translateY(-2px) scale(1.005);\n  border-color: rgba(57,255,20,0.30); \n  box-shadow: 0 0 0 1px rgba(57,255,20,0.15), 0 8px 32px rgba(0,0,0,0.40); \n}\n```\n\nHmm, the user said \"expand on a bit not just to a point\" — they want the marker to extend beyond the card slightly, not just to a point at the corner. The current code makes it 80x80 which is still a corner, just bigger.\n\nOK let me also check the `.card-outcome` class which is a similar pattern. I should update both.\n\nLet me also think about the box-shadow. The corner marker has a green glow box-shadow. On hover, the full border should also glow. The current glow values:\n- Default: `0 0 6px #39FF14, 0 0 14px rgba(57,255,20,0.55)`\n- Current hover: `0 0 8px #39FF14, 0 0 24px rgba(57,255,20,0.50), 0 0 48px rgba(57,255,20,0.25)`\n\nFor the new full-border hover, I want a similar but more spread glow.\n\nAlso, I should add `border-radius: 8px` on hover so the full border curves around the card's rounded corners.\n\nWait, the card itself has `border-radius: 8px`. The `::before` is positioned at top: -1px, left: -1px with the card's 8px border-radius affecting its top-left corner (the L uses border-top-left-radius: 8px). When the `::before` expands to full size, its border-radius should also be 8px to match the card.\n\nOK let me write the patch. I need to update:\n1. `.card::before` and `.card:hover::before`\n2. `.card-outcome::before` and `.card-outcome:hover::before`\n\nAnd maybe also `.card:hover` and `.card-outcome:hover` for the slight overshoot transform on the card itself.\n\nLet me also think about the `perk-card` and other cards. The user said \"for each\" — let me check what other card types exist.\n\nLooking at the screenshot, the BYOC card is `.card`. There are also `.card-outcome` and `.perk-card` and the inline-styled credits cards.\n\nLet me check `.perk-card` and the credits cards.",
