      "text": "cool go ahead and fix it and then find out if the appointment link is ready:\n\nSince I cannot execute external Python scripts against live web APIs from my\r\ncurrent environment, you will need to run this script locally [1.2.6].\r\n\r\nHere is the complete, ready-to-run Python script with your actual API key,\r\ndatabase name, and username pre-configured [1.1.9, 1.2.6, 1.2.7]:\r\n\r\nStep 1: Save the Script\r\n\r\nCopy the code block below and save it as a file named odoo_cleanup.py on your\r\nlocal machine:\r\n\r\nimport xmlrpc.client\r\n\r\n# Your configured Odoo database details\r\nurl = \"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com\"\r\ndb = \"andiekobbie\"\r\nusername = \"andiekobbietks@outlook.com\"\r\npassword = \"4a4b79c4fa6716a3f294cb7279b24105218906d5\"  # Your active API Key\r\n\r\n# 1. Authenticate to retrieve your User ID (UID)\r\ncommon = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\"{url}/xmlrpc/2/common\")\r\ntry:\r\n    uid = common.authenticate(db, username, password, {})\r\nexcept Exception as e:\r\n    raise Exception(f\"Failed to connect to the authentication endpoint: {e}\")\r\n\r\nif not uid:\r\n    raise Exception(\"Authentication failed. Please verify your API Key and email address.\")\r\n\r\nprint(f\"Authenticated successfully as User ID: {uid}\")\r\n\r\n# 2. Connect to the main object endpoint\r\nmodels = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\"{url}/xmlrpc/2/object\")\r\n\r\n# 3. These parent modules will be uninstalled.\r\n# Odoo's cascading logic will automatically pull down all sub-modules\r\n# (such as To-Do, Dashboards, and Timesheets) that rely on them.\r\nparent_modules_to_uninstall = [\r\n    \"project\",      # Uninstalls Project, To-Do, Timesheets\r\n    \"account\",      # Uninstalls Invoicing\r\n    \"hr\",           # Uninstalls Employees, Skills Management\r\n    \"sign\",         # Uninstalls Sign\r\n    \"purchase\",     # Uninstalls Purchase\r\n    \"helpdesk\",     # Uninstalls Helpdesk\r\n    \"planning\",     # Uninstalls Planning\r\n    \"survey\",       # Uninstalls Surveys\r\n    \"knowledge\",    # Uninstalls Knowledge\r\n]\r\n\r\n# 4. Search for the active records in your database\r\nmodule_records = models.execute_kw(\r\n    db, uid, password,\r\n    'ir.module.module', 'search_read',\r\n    [[['name', 'in', parent_modules_to_uninstall], ['state', '=', 'installed']]],\r\n    {'fields': ['id', 'name', 'shortdesc']}\r\n)\r\n\r\nif not module_records:\r\n    print(\"\\nNo removable parent modules found. Your database is already cleaned up!\")\r\nelse:\r\n    print(f\"\\nFound {len(module_records)} modules to uninstall:\")\r\n    for rec in module_records:\r\n        print(f\" - {rec['shortdesc']} ({rec['name']})\")\r\n    \r\n    # Extract the database IDs for the modules\r\n    record_ids = [rec['id'] for rec in module_records]\r\n    \r\n    print(\"\\nTriggering uninstallation...\")\r\n    try:\r\n        # This call processes the uninstallation and forces a database reload.\r\n        # It is normal if the connection resets or times out during this step.\r\n        models.execute_kw(\r\n            db, uid, password,\r\n            'ir.module.module', 'button_immediate_uninstall',\r\n            [record_ids]\r\n        )\r\n        print(\"Uninstallation completed successfully.\")\r\n    except Exception as e:\r\n        # The uninstallation triggers a server reboot/registry reload,\r\n        # which commonly drops active connections. This is normal.\r\n        print(\"\\nDatabase registry is currently reloading. This is expected.\")\r\n        print(\"Wait 30-60 seconds, then refresh your Odoo browser tab to verify.\")\r\n\r\nStep 2: Run the Script\r\n\r\nOpen your terminal or command prompt, navigate to the folder where you saved the\r\nfile, and execute it [1.2.6]:\r\n\r\npython3 odoo_cleanup.py\r\n\r\n(If your environment uses the standard alias, you can use python odoo_cleanup.py\r\ninstead) [1.2.6].\r\n\r\nOnce the script finishes running, wait about 30 to 60 seconds for Odoo to\r\nrebuild its database registry, then refresh your browser tab on\r\nhttps://andiekobbie.odoo.com/odoo [1.1.9, 1.2.7]. Your dashboard will be cleared\r\nof the unnecessary apps [1.1.4].\n\n<system-reminder>\n<agent-context>\n  agent: Mavis\n  agentName: mavis\n  SESSION ROLE: root\n  YOUR SESSION ID: mvs_8d6cdf45af11451ca152d51c37e4fa64\n  YOUR AGENT ROOT SESSION: mvs_d12969f76d564c59a7d5be05b0fd5bdf\n  YOUR WORKSPACE DIRECTORY: C:\\Users\\LLM-Test\\.mavis\\sessions\\mvs_8d6cdf45af11451ca152d51c37e4fa64\\workspace\n  IS_DEFAULT_WORKSPACE: true\n  date: 2026-06-24 01:41:33 (Europe/London, UTC+1)\n</agent-context>\n\n<windows-behavior>\nReminder — your shell is PowerShell, NOT bash. Do NOT use `&&`, `ls -la`,\n`head`, `tail`, `grep`, `wc`. Use `;`, `Get-ChildItem`, `Select-Object`,\n`Select-String` instead. If `bash` produces garbled/WSL output, switch to\n`node`/`python` immediately — max 2 retries before changing approach.\n</windows-behavior>\n</system-reminder>",
