ct to the home page. For a published one, it should return 200 with the booking page.\n\nLet me test the URL pattern anyway. If the type is in DRAFT, the URL will probably 404. But I can test the URL structure to know what the published URL would be.\n\nActually, let me just do this:\n1. Test the URL `https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/appointment/1` with HEAD/GET\n2. If 200, the URL pattern is correct (and even in DRAFT, the URL is reachable)\n3. If 404, the URL might be different\n4. Report to user\n\nLet me do this.\n\nWait, I also need to think about: should I publish the appointment type for the user? It's a single click in Odoo. I can do it via the API:\n- `models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, 'appointment.type', 'write', [[1], {'is_published': True}])`\n\nBut the user only asked me to:\n1. Run the cleanup (done)\n2. Check if the appointment link is ready (done — it's not)\n\nThey didn't ask me to publish it. Let me NOT auto-publish, but offer to do so.\n\nLet me verify the URL pattern first, then report.",
