      "text": "`/odoo/appointment/1` is a 303 redirect — it's the Odoo backend requiring login. Not the public URL.\n\nFor Odoo Online (hosted), the public appointment URL is typically:\n- `https://<dbname>.odoo.com/appointment/<id>` — but this returned 404\n\nLet me check more URL patterns. Or query the appointment type for its actual public URL.\n\nActually, for Odoo Appointment module, when an appointment type is published, Odoo generates a \"share link\" that looks like:\n- `https://<dbname>.odoo.com/appointment/<id>` (for default)\n- Or with a custom website domain if configured\n\nThe 404 on `/appointment/1` could mean:\n- The URL pattern is different\n- The appointment type is in DRAFT, so the URL doesn't work\n- The URL needs a slug like `/appointment/1-discovery-consultation`\n\nLet me query the appointment.type for the actual public URL. The field might be `website_url` or it might need to be constructed from the slug.\n\nLet me also check the appointment.type for `access_token` or `website_url` fields.",
