      "type": "thought",
      "text": "OK so the user is sharing:\n\n1. A working appointment booking link: `https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd` — this is a SHAREABLE booking link (different from the appointment TYPE URL I found earlier). The share link pattern is `/book/<token>` and they have one ready.\n\n2. An Odoo error screenshot showing:\n   - \"Oops! Something went wrong...\"\n   - \"Odoo Client Error\"\n   - \"UncaughtPromiseError > TypeError\"\n   - \"Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'length')\"\n   - \"TourService.getTour\" at `web.assets_web.min.js:12212:16`\n   - \"TourService.resumeTour\" at `web.assets_web.min.js:12219:119`\n   - Occurred on andiekobbie.odoo.com on 24/Jun/2026 00:47:01\n\n3. User's asks:\n   - \"fix the odoo site if thats active and do what u need to do to it so its a lot like calendly\" — they want the Odoo appointment page to look/feel like Calendly\n   - \"and my odoo link as u cans ee can preview fine\" — the link works for them, they can preview\n\nSo the two main things to do:\n1. **Fix the Odoo error** — the `TourService.getTour` error. This is a known Odoo issue. The Tour service is part of Odoo's guided tour/onboarding system. The error `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'length')` in `TourService.getTour` typically happens when:\n   - There's a stale browser cache with old tour data\n   - The tour data in `ir.model.data` or `tour` model is corrupted\n   - A custom module or theme is interfering\n   - A new module was just installed/uninstalled and the registry is still loading\n\n   Given that we just uninstalled 9 modules a few minutes ago, the registry might still be settling. The error could be transient. But to fix it properly, we might need to:\n   - Clear the browser's local storage for the Odoo domain\n   - Or check if there's stale tour data in the database\n   - Or restart the Odoo service (which is not under our control since it's hosted)\n   \n2. **Make the appointment page look like Calendly** — the user wants the Odoo booking page to have a Calendly-like UI/UX. Calendly's design has:\n   - A profile picture and intro on the left\n   - A clean card with available time slots on the right\n   - Green accent colors\n   - Simple date/time selection\n   \n   I can:\n   - Customize the Odoo Appointment page via:\n     - Editing the appointment type's title, description, and branding\n     - Adding a profile image for the host\n     - Setting the colors\n     - Adding a custom message\n   - Or apply a theme to the Odoo website\n\n3. **The user has a /book/27e80afd link that's working** — this is a SHARE link, different from the appointment type URL. The share link bypasses the \"is_published\" flag (it's a public access token). This is the link they want to share with customers.\n\nLet me look at this more carefully. The appointment URL pattern `/book/<token>` is the \"shareable\" link. The user wants to use this for their customers. The error is happening when they (or someone) tries to use the link.\n\nWait, the error screenshot shows the Odoo BACKEND, not the booking page. The error is in the TourService which is part of the Odoo web client. So when someone opens an Odoo backend page, the tour service tries to resume a tour and crashes.\n\nThis is likely because:\n- The Odoo registry is still loading from the module uninstall\n- The `tour` model has stale references to modules that no longer exist\n- Or the browser has a stale session\n\nTo fix this:\n1. **Wait for the registry to finish reloading** — it might take a few more minutes after the 9 module uninstalls\n2. **Clear the browser cache and local storage** for andiekobbie.odoo.com\n3. **Check if there are stale tours in the database** that reference uninstalled modules — if so, delete them\n4. **Update the Appointment type** to make the share link more Calendly-like\n\nLet me think about the Calendly-like customization. I can:\n\nA. Update the appointment type:\n- Set a clean title and subtitle\n- Add a description\n- Set the host's name and photo\n- Add a custom message\n- Set the duration and other parameters\n- Customize the colors (use AKcloud green #39FF14 or a similar palette)\n\nB. The share link with token `27e80afd` is a specific resource. I can:\n- Query the Odoo API to find this specific appointment resource\n- Update its settings\n\nC. For the \"Calendly-like\" design, Odoo's appointment page is fairly customizable:\n- You can set the appointment_intro, appointment_invite_html\n- The page has a left column (host info) and right column (booking form)\n- You can use the website builder to customize\n\nLet me approach this:\n1. First, query the Odoo API to understand the current appointment setup\n2. Find the specific share link `27e80afd` \n3. Look at what customizations are possible\n4. Make Calendly-like improvements:\n   - Set a clean, professional intro\n   - Add a host profile (name, image, role)\n   - Add a custom message\n   - Set the page colors to match AKcloud brand\n   - Add the AKcloud logo\n\nFor the error:\n- The TourService error is likely transient from the module uninstall\n- I can clear stale tours via the API\n- Or just wait for the registry to settle\n\nLet me first investigate the current state via the API.\n\nPlan:\n1. Query Odoo for the current appointment types and the share link `27e80afd`\n2. Check for stale tours\n3. Update the appointment to be Calendly-like\n4. Verify the share link works\n5. Report back\n\nLet me also remember: I should NOT echo the API key in my response. I'll keep using it via the script.\n\nLet me start by writing a script to investigate the current state.\n\nActually, I should also consider: the user said \"fix the odoo site if thats active and do what u need to do to it so its a lot like calendly and my odoo link as u cans ee can preview fine\"\n\nThe user CAN preview the link fine. But the Odoo BACKEND (the admin area) is showing an error. The share link might be working, but the backend is broken.\n\nSo:\n1. Fix the Odoo backend error (TourService)\n2. Customize the appointment page to look like Calendly\n3. Verify the share link still works\n\nLet me proceed.\n\nStep 1: Investigate. I'll write a script that:\n- Queries the appointment types and finds the one with share_token 27e80afd\n- Checks for stale tours\n- Returns the current configuration\n\nStep 2: Make Calendly-like customizations. Based on what I find, I'll update the appointment type with:\n- Professional intro\n- Host profile\n- Custom message\n- Branding\n\nStep 3: Fix the TourService error. I'll:\n- Find stale tours\n- Delete them (or fix the references)\n\nLet me start.\n\nWait, I should also look at the share link specifically. The share token `27e80afd` is what I should target. Let me query the Odoo API for appointment types with this token.\n\nActually, the share link pattern `/book/<token>` is typically for `calendar.event` or `appointment.booking` records. Let me check the Odoo Appointment module structure.\n\nIn Odoo's `website_appointment` module:\n- An appointment type has a `share_link` or similar field that generates the `/book/<token>` URL\n- The token is usually stored on the appointment type record\n\nLet me query the appointment type and look for the share token. The field might be `access_token` or `share_token`.\n\nActually, looking at my earlier output, the appointment.type had `access_token` listed as a field. Let me check if the existing appointment type's access_token matches `27e80afd`.\n\nWait, in my earlier script, I queried fields with \"access\" in the name and got nothing. The token `27e80afd` might be in a different field. Let me query for all fields of the appointment type.\n\nActually, let me just write a script that:\n1. Finds the appointment type\n2. Lists all its fields\n3. Looks for the share token\n\nThen I can update the appointment type with Calendly-like customizations.\n\nOK let me proceed. I'll write a single script that:\n1. Authenticates\n2. Finds the appointment type (by ID 1) and all its fields\n3. Checks for stale tours (model `web_tour.tour` or `ir.model.data` references)\n4. Returns findings\n\nThen I'll decide on customizations.\n\nLet me also think about: the user wants the Odoo appointment page to look like Calendly. What are the key features of Calendly's design?\n- Clean, minimal interface\n- Large profile photo on the left\n- Name and role/title below the photo\n- Description\n- Available time slots in a card on the right\n- Color customization (usually a single accent color)\n- Calendar view with date picker\n- Time slot buttons\n\nOdoo's appointment page has:\n- A host info section (with photo, name, role)\n- A date picker\n- A time slot grid\n- Customizable CSS\n\nTo make it Calendly-like, I can:\n- Set a clean intro message\n- Add a profile photo for the host\n- Set a single accent color\n- Customize the CSS (via the Odoo theme system)\n- Set the appointment type title to something clean\n\nLet me check what the user has currently and what I can change.\n\nFor the API call, I'll need to:\n1. Use the same auth (xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy)\n2. Update the appointment type record\n\nFor making it \"Calendly-like\":\n- The Odoo Appointment page has many built-in features\n- I can customize via:\n  - appointment_intro (HTML/text)\n  - appointment_invite_html (custom HTML shown after booking)\n  - confirmation (custom confirmation message)\n  - Colors via the Odoo website theme (would need to use the website builder)\n  - The host's user_id and their profile photo\n\nLet me investigate first. Then make changes.\n\nFor the TourService error:\n- I can find tours in the database\n- The `web_tour.tour` model has the tours\n- Or the issue is with `ir.model.data` references\n\nLet me also see: the error trace shows `web.assets_web.min.js`. This is the compiled Odoo JavaScript. The error is in `TourService.getTour` which is the JS that loads tours from the backend. The error is `Cannot read properties of undefined (reading 'length')` — likely it's trying to access `tours.something.length` but tours is undefined.\n\nThis could mean:\n- The /web/tours endpoint is failing to return data\n- The tours XML/JS data is corrupted\n\nTo fix, I can:\n- Clear the tour data (set all tours to archived/draft)\n- Or fix the underlying data issue\n\nLet me also see if there are stale tours. The web_tour.tour model in Odoo has a list of tours. If one references a module that was just uninstalled, it might cause issues.\n\nOK let me just start. I'll write a single investigation script and then make changes.",
