      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Good, I have the diagnosis output from before. Looking at the user's HTML paste, the key insight is:\n\n```json\n\"current_tour\": {\n    \"name\": \"web_studio_new_app_tour\",\n    \"custom\": false,\n    \"url\": \"/odoo/action-studio?mode=home_menu\",\n    \"steps\": [],\n    \"rainbowManMessage\": \"<span><b>Good job!</b> You went through all steps of this tour.</span>\"\n}\n```\n\nThe tour has `steps: []` (empty array). The tour is `web_studio_new_app_tour` from the Studio module. The rainbow message says the user already completed this tour. But the state is stuck.\n\nThe fix is to clear this tour. There are several approaches:\n\n1. **Clear the tour state for the user** - delete the tour.tracker record\n2. **Disable tours** - set `tour_enabled = false` for the user\n3. **Mark the tour as completed/skipped** - update the record\n4. **Clear the browser's local storage** for the Odoo domain (user side)\n\nLooking at the Odoo source, the `tour_enabled` flag is in the session_info, which is set when the user logs in. It can be controlled by:\n- A field on `res.users` (some versions)\n- A system parameter `tour_enabled` or `disable_tour`\n- The `tour.tracker` model that tracks progress\n\nLet me try:\n1. Search for `tour.tracker` model\n2. Check if `tour_enabled` is a field on `res.users`\n3. If `tour.tracker` exists, delete the entry for the user\n\nAlso for the share token `27e80afd`:\n- It's not in the appointment.type fields I checked\n- It might be in a related model (e.g., `appointment.invite` or `appointment.share`)\n- Or it might be the access_token of a specific `appointment.type` (but the type ID 1 has a different token)\n\nLet me search more broadly.\n\nAlso, looking at the user's HTML again, I see the session shows:\n- `partner_display_name`: \"AndieKobbiePics, Andrea Enning\"\n- `username`: \"andiekobbietks@outlook.com\"\n- `tz`: \"Europe/London\"\n- `db`: \"andiekobbie\"\n\nSo the user's name is \"Andrea Enning\" and the company is \"AndieKobbie\". The appointment is for \"Discovery Consultation & More\".\n\nLet me now write a comprehensive script that:\n1. Searches for the share token 27e80afd in multiple places\n2. Diagnoses the tour issue\n3. Provides options to fix both\n\nFor the tour, let me think about the cleanest fix. The `current_tour` is in the session_info and is set on login. It comes from `tour.tracker` or similar. If I can delete the tracker record, the tour won't appear in the next session.\n\nBut actually, looking at the structure:\n- `current_tour` is set in the session_info when a tour is in progress\n- The `steps: []` suggests the tour is completed but the tracker wasn't cleared\n- The fix: delete the tracker record OR mark the tour as completed\n\nLet me look for the model that stores this. In Odoo, the model is `web_tour.tour` for the tour definition and `tour.tracker` for the user's progress. Let me check.\n\nOK let me just write the script and run it.",
