    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a clear picture:\n\n**1. Tour diagnosis:**\n- `web_tour.tour` has 2 tours: `web_studio_new_app_tour` (id 16) and `discuss_channel_tour` (id 1)\n- Both have `step_ids: []` (empty) and `user_consumed_ids: []` (empty)\n- These tours have empty steps, which is causing the `getTour` error\n- The `tour_enabled` is a field on `res.users` and is `True` for the current user\n\nThe fix: Set `tour_enabled = False` on the user. That should prevent the TourService from trying to resume tours and causing the error.\n\n**2. Appointment.type #1:**\n- Name: \"Discovery Consultation & More\"\n- Duration: 0.75 minutes (that's weird — 0.75 min? probably should be in hours, so 0.75h = 45min?)\n- Min hours: 1.0\n- Max days: 14\n- Location: \"AndieKobbieTech, City Campus, Usk Way, Newport NP20 2BP\"\n- Host user: None\n- No intro HTML, no invite HTML\n- message_confirmation: False\n- is_published: False\n- Has image fields (image_128, 256, 512, 1024, 1920) for the host photo\n- Has message_intro, message_confirmation (HTML fields)\n\n**3. Share token 27e80afd:**\n- Not found in the database\n- It's likely generated on-the-fly by the URL routing\n- Or it's stored in a model I didn't check\n\nLooking at Odoo 19's appointment module, the share token pattern `/book/<token>` might be in a different model. Let me check `appointment.share` or similar.\n\nActually, looking at the Odoo source code, the share token for appointments in newer versions is typically:\n- Generated from the appointment.type using a unique token\n- Stored as `access_token` on the appointment.type record\n\nBut the field doesn't exist on the type. Let me check related models.\n\nActually wait — the URL `/book/27e80afd` might be the link to a SPECIFIC appointment booking, not the type. In Odoo, when someone books, they get a confirmation link with a token. That token would be in `calendar.event` (which I checked but found nothing) or `appointment.booking`.\n\nBut the user said this is a shareable link that they can preview fine. So it's a share link to the appointment TYPE, not a specific booking.\n\nLet me look for it in different fields/models. Actually, looking at the URL structure `/book/<token>`, this is the public booking URL. In Odoo 19, this is the URL pattern for `appointment.booking` records OR for `appointment.type` access tokens.\n\nLet me search more broadly. I'll check:\n- `appointment.type` with different field names\n- `calendar.event` (already did)\n- Look for all models with \"share\" or \"book\" in the name\n\nActually wait, the user's earlier comment was that they can preview the link fine. So the link works. They want it to look like Calendly. So the priority is:\n1. Customize the existing appointment.type to be Calendly-like\n2. The share token exists (somewhere) and works\n\nFor the share token, I might not need to find where it's stored — the user already has a working link. I just need to update the appointment type to make that link's page look better.\n\nLet me focus on:\n1. **Fix the tour error** - set `tour_enabled = False` on the user\n2. **Customize the appointment type**:\n   - Set a clean, Calendly-like intro (message_intro)\n   - Add a custom confirmation message (message_confirmation)\n   - Set a proper duration (0.75h = 45min, or whatever's appropriate)\n   - Add the host user\n   - Set the host photo\n   - Publish the appointment type (is_published = True) so it shows up\n\nWait, the user said they have a working share link `/book/27e80afd`. This means the link is already live, even if `is_published` is False. The share link bypasses the published check because it has a direct token.\n\nActually, looking more carefully at Odoo's appointment module:\n- The `/appointment/<slug>` URL requires the type to be published\n- The `/book/<token>` URL uses a specific access token (might not require published)\n\nLet me verify this by testing the URL.\n\nFor the Calendly-like customization, I need to:\n1. Set the host (user_id) to the current user (Andrea) so the host photo and name show up\n2. Add a profile photo for the host (the image_128 field)\n3. Set a proper duration (in hours, like 0.5 for 30 min, 1 for 60 min)\n4. Add a clean intro message (message_intro)\n5. Add a custom confirmation (message_confirmation)\n6. Set appointment_intro_html (additional customization)\n\nLet me also think about how Odoo's appointment page renders:\n- Host info (name, photo, role) on the left or top\n- Date picker\n- Time slot grid\n- \"Book\" button\n- After booking, confirmation page\n\nFor Calendly-like, I'd want:\n- Clean intro\n- Time zone display\n- Duration clearly shown\n- Friendly tone\n- Branded colors\n\nThe colors in Odoo's appointment page are typically set via the website theme (not per-appointment-type). So I might not be able to set the AKcloud green directly. But I can:\n- Add the host's name and photo\n- Add a great intro message\n- Customize the confirmation\n- Set a clean duration\n\nLet me also check what `auto_confirm` and `is_always_confirm` mean.\n\nFor the tour fix, let me:\n1. Set `tour_enabled = False` on `res.users` for the current user\n2. This should prevent the TourService from trying to load tours on next login\n\nLet me also check if there's a way to delete the tour records. The `web_tour.tour` records are at the system level. Deleting them might not be appropriate (they're part of Odoo's core). Better to just disable tours for the user.\n\nOK let me write the next script that:\n1. Fixes the tour error\n2. Customizes the appointment type\n\nFor the Calendly-like customization, I need to be careful about:\n- The host user (should be Andrea, the current user)\n- The host photo (need to upload an image)\n- The intro text\n- The confirmation text\n- The duration\n\nFor the host photo, I need to upload an image. I don't have an image of Andrea. I could:\n- Skip the photo (just set the host user, the avatar will use initials or default)\n- Use a placeholder\n\nLet me just set the host user and skip the photo for now. The user can upload a photo via the Odoo UI later.\n\nActually, looking at the data: the user's partner_id is 3 (AndieKobbiePics, Andrea Enning). The user's avatar token is in the session. I can use that.\n\nBut for simplicity, let me just:\n1. Set the host (user_id = 2, Andrea)\n2. Set the duration to a proper value\n3. Set the intro and confirmation messages\n4. Publish the appointment type\n\nFor the message_intro (HTML), I'll write something Calendly-like:\n```html\n<div class=\"o_appointment_intro\">\n  <h2>Discovery Consultation</h2>\n  <p>30 minutes to explore how AKCloud can power your sovereign cloud journey. Bring questions about your workload, region, and budget — I'll bring answers.</p>\n</div>\n```\n\nFor message_confirmation:\n```html\n<div class=\"o_appointment_confirmation\">\n  <h3>You're booked</h3>\n  <p>Calendar invite on its way. Need to reschedule? Use the link in your email.</p>\n</div>\n```\n\nFor duration: the current value is 0.75. In Odoo, appointment_duration is in hours. 0.75 hours = 45 minutes. Let me make it 0.5 (30 min) for a \"Discovery Consultation\" feel, or keep 0.75 (45 min). Actually, 0.75 is fine for a consultation.\n\nLet me also think about Calendly's typical intro elements:\n- Welcome message\n- Time zone display\n- Duration\n- \"Book a time\" call to action\n- Maybe a note about what to expect\n\nLet me write a clean intro that matches Calendly's vibe.\n\nFor the fix script:\n1. Set res.users.tour_enabled = False\n2. Update appointment.type #1 with:\n   - user_id = 2 (Andrea)\n   - appointment_duration = 0.5 (30 min) - actually, let me keep 0.75 since the user already set it\n   - message_intro = \"<clean intro html>\"\n   - message_confirmation = \"<clean confirmation html>\"\n   - is_published = True (or leave False if they want to keep the share-token-only access)\n   - appointment_intro_html = similar (if it's a separate field)\n3. Verify the share link still works\n4. Verify the Odoo backend loads without the tour error\n\nWait — about is_published. The user said they have a working share link `/book/27e80afd`. If I publish the appointment type, it would also be accessible via `/appointment/discovery-consultation-more-1`. That's probably fine — it makes the appointment more discoverable.\n\nLet me also think about the host user. The `user_id` field is on `appointment.type` and points to a `res.users` record. The current user is uid=2 (Andrea). Let me set user_id = 2.\n\nWait, but the user might want to book the appointment FOR the user. The user_id is who the appointment is WITH. Setting it to Andrea makes sense.\n\nOK let me write the fix script.\n\nActually, one more thing about the tour error. The error happens in `TourService.getTour` and `TourService.resumeTour`. The user has `tour_enabled = True` and `current_tour` is set. The fix is to set `tour_enabled = False`.\n\nBut the `current_tour` is in the session info, computed at login. Even if I set `tour_enabled = False`, the current session might still try to resume. The user would need to:\n- Log out and log back in\n- Or clear the session\n\nOr I can also try to clear the `current_tour` somehow. But that's set by the server, not stored in a model.\n\nActually, the cleanest fix: set `tour_enabled = False`. On the next page load or login, the tour service won't try to resume the tour.\n\nBut wait, looking at the Odoo source:\n- The `tour_enabled` flag controls whether tours are shown\n- When False, the TourService shouldn't try to resume tours\n\nLet me set it to False and verify the backend loads.\n\nOK let me write the script.\n\nPlan:\n1. Set res.users.tour_enabled = False for the current user\n2. Update appointment.type #1:\n   - user_id = 2 (Andrea)\n   - message_intro = \"<calendly-like intro>\"\n   - message_confirmation = \"<calendly-like confirmation>\"\n   - Optionally is_published = True\n3. Test that the Odoo backend loads without error\n4. Test the share link\n\nLet me also be careful: the appointment type might have dependencies on other modules I uninstalled. Let me verify the appointment module is still working.\n\nActually, looking at the appointment.type data, it has fields like `message_intro`, `message_confirmation`, `image_*`, `user_id` — these are all from the appointment module. The fact that the type exists and I can read it means the module is functional. \n\nBut wait — the error in the user's screenshot was on the Odoo backend, not the appointment page. The backend tried to load the tour and crashed. If I set `tour_enabled = False`, the backend should load fine.\n\nThe share link `/book/27e80afd` is a public page (no login required). It doesn't use the tour service. So the share link might still work even with the tour error. But let me verify.\n\nOK let me write the fix script.",
