      "text": "Interesting findings:\n\n1. **`/book/27e80afd`**: Status 200, title \"Discovery Consultation & More | AndieKobbie\", has appointment markers, no tour markers. The share link works and shows the new appointment.\n\n2. **`/appointment/discovery-consultation-1`**: 404. The canonical URL is 404 because `is_published = False` and `website_published = False`. To make this URL work, I'd need to publish it. But the user said they want to keep the share-link-only access.\n\nWait, the share link title says \"Discovery Consultation & More\" — that's the OLD name. My write should have changed it to \"Discovery Consultation\". Let me check.\n\nHmm, the title shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\" — but I changed the name to \"Discovery Consultation\". Maybe the title is being generated from a different field, or the cache is stale.\n\nLet me also check the page content to see if my intro HTML and other customizations are showing up.\n\n3. **`/odoo` (backend)**: Status 200, title \"Login | AndieKobbie\". This means the backend is showing a login page (the user is not logged in via my unauthenticated request). The tour error was in the logged-in session, so I can't verify it via an unauthenticated request.\n\nBut since I set `tour_enabled = False`, the tour service should not try to load tours on the next login. This is the fix.\n\nFor the appointment title issue, let me check if there's a different field for the displayed title, or if it's cached.\n\nActually wait — the title is the `<title>` tag of the HTML page. It's set by the Odoo controller for the appointment page. The title comes from the appointment type's name field. So if the name is now \"Discovery Consultation\", the title should be \"Discovery Consultation | AndieKobbie\".\n\nBut the title is still \"Discovery Consultation & More | AndieKobbie\". Hmm.\n\nThis could be:\n- Caching issue (the page is cached)\n- The title comes from a different field\n- The Odoo controller uses a different mechanism for the title\n\nLet me check the raw HTML to see the title and look for the new intro HTML.\n\nActually, looking at the appointment type schema, there might be separate fields for:\n- `name` — the internal name\n- `displayed_name` or `website_name` — the public title\n\nLet me check the appointment.type for a website-related name field.\n\nAlso, the `is_published` is False, so the canonical URL `/appointment/discovery-consultation-1` returns 404. That's expected.\n\nBut the share link `/book/27e80afd` returns 200, which is what the user wants.\n\nLet me check the share link page content to see:\n1. Is the new title showing?\n2. Is the new intro HTML showing?\n3. Is the new duration showing?\n4. Is the new confirmation message in the data?\n\nLet me fetch the share link page and look for these markers.",
