    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Interesting findings:\n\n1. **Title and H1 still show \"Discovery Consultation & More\"** — the Odoo page is using a different field for the public title. My write changed the `name` field but the page is using something else.\n\n2. **H2 shows \"Discovery Consultation\"** — my intro HTML's H2 is rendering correctly!\n\n3. **My intro HTML is showing**: \"Exo 2\" font, \"Video call\" pill, \"30 minutes\" appears 3 times. The intro section is working.\n\n4. **Old data still showing**: AndieKobbieTech, City Campus, Usk Way, NP20 2BP — the location field. I didn't change this (left it as the original).\n\n5. **\"Sovereign cloud journey\"** is absent — but wait, this string contains \"cloud\" which might have been a special char. Let me check.\n\n6. **Confirmation message not on the page** — the message_confirmation field is for after booking, so it wouldn't be on the initial page. That's correct.\n\n7. **No tour markers** — the tour issue is no longer in the page HTML. \n\nSo the main issue is: the H1 and `<title>` still show \"Discovery Consultation & More\". My change to `name` didn't propagate to the public title.\n\nLooking at the Odoo Appointment module, the public title likely comes from a different field. Common possibilities:\n- `displayed_name` — the public-facing name\n- `name` should be it, but maybe it's overridden by another field\n- The page might be cached\n\nLet me check the appointment type fields for a \"title\" or \"displayed_name\" field. Actually, the public title is usually just `name`. The issue might be that:\n- The page is server-side rendered and uses a cache\n- The title field is something else\n\nLet me also check: when Odoo renders the appointment page, it might use `appointment_type.name` or there might be a separate `displayed_name` field.\n\nLet me query the appointment.type for all string fields.\n\nAlso, \"Sovereign cloud journey\" is the text I put in the intro — let me check. The intro has:\n```\n\"<strong>30 minutes</strong> to map your sovereign cloud journey — architecture, region, budget...\"\n```\n\nSo \"sovereign cloud journey\" should be in the HTML. But the marker search said it's absent. Wait, the search was for \"Sovereign cloud journey\" (capital S). The actual text is \"sovereign cloud journey\" (lowercase). Let me re-check.\n\nYes — case sensitivity. The search for \"Sovereign cloud journey\" (capital S) found 0, but the lowercase \"sovereign cloud journey\" is in the HTML. My grep was case-sensitive.\n\nOK so the intro IS rendering correctly. The main remaining issue is the page title and H1.\n\nLet me check what field controls the H1/title. In Odoo's appointment page template, it might use:\n- `<title t-out=\"appointment_type.name\">` — uses `name`\n- `<h1 t-out=\"appointment_type.name\">` — uses `name`\n\nBut the H1 still shows the OLD name. That's strange — unless the page is cached.\n\nOdoo's website pages have caching. The `/book/27e80afd` page might be cached. Let me check if there's a cache buster or a way to invalidate it.\n\nActually wait — the new H2 shows \"Discovery Consultation\" (from my intro HTML), but the H1 shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\" (the old name). So the change to `name` was written but not reflected in the H1.\n\nThis means:\n- The `name` field is now \"Discovery Consultation\" (in the DB)\n- But the H1 on the page shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\"\n- This could be:\n  - Caching (browser, CDN, or Odoo website cache)\n  - The H1 uses a different field\n\nLet me check if the appointment type's `name` is actually \"Discovery Consultation\" now (re-read from DB).\n\nThen let me try to invalidate the page cache.",
