    {
      "type": "answer",
      "text": "The DB has `name = 'Discovery Consultation'` correctly, so the share link page is just serving a stale cache. Let me test with a cache-buster and look for the right way to invalidate.",
      "timestamp": 1782263327436
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "OK so:\n- The DB has `name = 'Discovery Consultation'` correctly\n- But the share link page still shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\" in title and H1\n- That's definitely a cache issue\n\nThe website.page field `cache_template` doesn't exist. Let me try a different field name. Odoo's website.page usually has fields like:\n- id\n- url\n- name\n- website_id\n- view_id\n- is_published\n- cache_key (in newer versions)\n- header_color\n- ...\n\nLet me try just `id`, `url`, `name`. Also, for clearing the cache, I can use:\n- `website.page` clear cache method\n- Or clear the website's cache directly\n\nActually, for Odoo 19, the website cache is typically stored in `ir.attachment` or `ir.ui.view`. Let me try a different approach:\n\n1. Just check the website.page record for the appointment\n2. Look at the `view_id` linked to the page\n3. Invalidate the view cache by writing to it (bumping the write_date)\n\nOr simpler: I can just re-fetch the page with a cache-busting URL parameter.\n\nWait, I should also try fetching `/book/27e80afd?cb=<timestamp>` to see if the page is actually using a stale cache.",
      "timestamp": 1782263344751
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"$urls = @(\\n  \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd\\\",\\n  \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd?cb=1\\\",\\n  \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd?nocache=$((Get-Date).Ticks)\\\"\\n)\\nforeach ($u in $urls) {\\n  $r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri $u -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 15 -Headers @{\\\"Cache-Control\\\"=\\\"no-cache\\\"; \\\"Pragma\\\"=\\\"no-cache\\\"}\\n  $title = (Select-String -InputObject $r.Content -Pattern \\\"<title>[^<]*</title>\\\" -AllMatches).Matches[0].Value\\n  $h1 = (Select-String -InputObject $r.Content -Pattern \\\"<h1[^>]*>[^<]+</h1>\\\" -AllMatches).Matches[0].Value\\n  Write-Host \\\"  $($u.Substring(8,50))\\u2026\\\"\\n  Write-Host \\\"     $title\\\"\\n  Write-Host \\\"     $h1\\\"\\n}\", \"timeout\": 45000, \"description\": \"Check if the page is cached (test with cache-busters)\"}",
      "output": "Eccezione durante la chiamata di \"Substring\" con \"2\" argomento/i: \"Index e length devono fare riferimento a una \r\n  .\n     <title>Discovery Consultation &amp; More | AndieKobbie</title>\nposizione nella stringa.\r\nNome parametro: length\"\r\nIn riga:10 car:19\r\n+   Write-Host \"  $($u.Substring(8,50)).\"\r\n+                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (:) [], MethodInvocationException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : ArgumentOutOfRangeException\r\n \r\n     <h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation &amp; More</h1>\nEccezione durante la chiamata di \"Substring\" con \"2\" argomento/i: \"Index e length devono fare riferimento a una \r\n  .\n     <title>Discovery Consultation &amp; More | AndieKobbie</title>\nposizione nella stringa.\r\nNome parametro: length\"\r\nIn riga:10 car:19\r\n+   Write-Host \"  $($u.Substring(8,50)).\"\r\n+                   ~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~\r\n    + CategoryInfo          : NotSpecified: (:) [], MethodInvocationException\r\n    + FullyQualifiedErrorId : ArgumentOutOfRangeException\r\n \r\n     <h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation &amp; More</h1>\n  andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd?nocache=6391786.\n     <title>Discovery Consultation &amp; More | AndieKobbie</title>\n     <h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation &amp; More</h1>\n",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782263351951
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Even with a cache-buster query string, the title and H1 are still \"Discovery Consultation & More\". So the page is NOT serving from a stale cache — the controller is actually generating the page with that title.\n\nThat means the title comes from a DIFFERENT field than `name`. Let me check the appointment type for the actual title field.\n\nLooking at the HTML I captured earlier:\n```html\n<title>Discovery Consultation & More | AndieKobbie</title>\n<h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation & More</h1>\n```\n\nThese match. So the page title and H1 use the same field. And that field has the value \"Discovery Consultation & More\" (the OLD name).\n\nThe DB shows `name = 'Discovery Consultation'`. So the H1/title is NOT using `name`.\n\nThis is strange. Let me look at the Odoo Appointment page template. The title in `<title>` and the H1 might be coming from:\n- A `displayed_name` field (which I tried but it doesn't exist)\n- A `name_with_duration` field\n- A website page attribute\n- An attribute on the appointment_type that's auto-generated\n\nLet me look for string fields on appointment.type that contain the old title.\n\nActually, looking at the appointment.type schema I dumped earlier, the string/char fields are many. Let me look for fields that could be the title:\n- `name` (already changed to \"Discovery Consultation\")\n- `displayed_name` (not a real field)\n- `name_with_duration` (not a real field)\n- `appointment_duration_formatted` (\"30 mins\" - not the title)\n\nWait, maybe the page is using the OLD H1 that was set as a custom override. Or maybe there's a translation issue. The H1 was there before my change, so maybe it was set somewhere else.\n\nLet me check:\n1. Is there a translation record (ir.translation) for appointment.type with the old name?\n2. Is there a website.page record that has a custom H1?\n3. Is there a `display_name` or similar computed field that's not picking up the new value?\n\nActually, the `name` field was just changed in the DB. The Odoo computed field `display_name` (which is auto-generated for all models) would use `name`. So the H1 should be \"Discovery Consultation\" now.\n\nBut it's showing \"Discovery Consultation & More\". This means the H1 is using a different source.\n\nWait — could it be that the H1 in the Odoo Appointment template is hardcoded, and the controller is passing the OLD value somehow? Or the template is using a translated value?\n\nLet me check for translations.\n\nActually, you know what — let me just look at the raw HTML of the share link page to see what's around the H1. Maybe there's a clue about which field it's using.",
      "timestamp": 1782263367824
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "bash",
      "code": "{\"command\": \"$r = Invoke-WebRequest -Uri \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd\\\" -UseBasicParsing -TimeoutSec 15\\n$h = $r.Content\\n# Get context around the H1\\n$idx = $h.IndexOf(\\\"<h1\\\")\\nif ($idx -gt 0) {\\n  Write-Host \\\"=== H1 context (400 chars) ===\\\"\\n  Write-Host $h.Substring([Math]::Max(0,$idx-200), 400)\\n}\\nWrite-Host \\\"\\\"\\n# Get context around the <title>\\n$idx = $h.IndexOf(\\\"<title>\\\")\\nif ($idx -gt 0) {\\n  Write-Host \\\"=== title context (300 chars) ===\\\"\\n  Write-Host $h.Substring([Math]::Max(0,$idx-100), 300)\\n}\", \"timeout\": 30000, \"description\": \"Inspect H1/title context to find the source field\"}",
      "output": "=== H1 context (400 chars) ===\n>\n                                    <div class=\"clearfix\"></div>\n                                    <div class=\"o_appointment_upcoming_appointment_alert\"></div>\n                                    <h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation &amp; More</h1>\n                                    <div class=\"row\">\n                                        <div class=\"o_appointment_cal\n\n=== title context (300 chars) ===\n>\n        <link rel=\"apple-touch-icon\" href=\"/web/image/website/1/favicon?unique=914ea55\"/>\n        <title>Discovery Consultation &amp; More | AndieKobbie</title>\n        <link type=\"image/x-icon\" rel=\"shortcut icon\" href=\"/web/image/website/1/favicon?unique=914ea55\"/>\n        <link rel=\"preload\" hr\n",
      "status": "success",
      "timestamp": 1782263374187
    },
    {
      "type": "thought",
      "text": "The H1 and title are using the same value: \"Discovery Consultation & More\". My change to the `name` field didn't take effect for the public page. \n\nLet me look at the Odoo Appointment template. In Odoo's `website_appointment` module, the appointment page template uses something like:\n```xml\n<title t-field=\"appointment_type.name\">...</title>\n<h1 t-field=\"appointment_type.name\">...</h1>\n```\n\nIf this is the case, the H1/title should pick up the new `name`. But it doesn't.\n\nPossible reasons:\n1. **Odoo has a website.page record** that overrides the default template for this specific URL, with the H1 hardcoded.\n2. **There's a translation** that overrides the value.\n3. **The H1 is using a different field** that I haven't identified.\n\nLet me check `website.page` and `ir.translation`.\n\nActually, looking at the URL `/book/27e80afd`, this is a custom route, not the standard `/appointment/<slug>` route. It might have its own page record in `website.page` with a custom H1 hardcoded.\n\nLet me also check `ir.translation` for the appointment.type name.\n\nWait, looking at the appointment module's code, the `/book/<token>` route might render a different page than `/appointment/<slug>`. Let me check if there's a `website.page` for `/book/27e80afd` specifically.\n\nLet me also check the Odoo page templates. The \"Discovery Consultation & More\" might be a website.page's H1 that's hardcoded in the page body.",
      "timestamp": 1782263395891
    },
    {
      "type": "action",
      "tool": "write",
      "code": "{\"content\": \"\\\"\\\"\\\"Find the source of the stale \\\"Discovery Consultation & More\\\" H1.\\n\\nCONTAINS LIVE ODOO API KEY.\\n\\\"\\\"\\\"\\nimport xmlrpc.client\\n\\nURL = \\\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com\\\"\\nDB = \\\"andiekobbie\\\"\\nUSERNAME = \\\"andiekobbietks@outlook.com\\\"\\nAPI_KEY = \\\"4a4b79c4fa6716a3f294cb7279b24105218906d5\\\"  # noqa: S105\\n\\ncommon = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\\\"{URL}/xmlrpc/2/common\\\")\\nuid = common.authenticate(DB, USERNAME, API_KEY, {})\\nmodels = xmlrpc.client.ServerProxy(f\\\"{URL}/xmlrpc/2/object\\\")\\n\\n# 1. Check website.page\\nprint(\\\"[1] website.page records\\\")\\ntry:\\n    pages = models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \\\"website.page\\\", \\\"search_read\\\",\\n        [[]], {\\\"fields\\\": [\\\"id\\\", \\\"url\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"is_published\\\", \\\"website_id\\\", \\\"view_id\\\"]})\\n    for p in pages:\\n        print(f\\\"  [{p['id']:>3}] {p['url']:<60}  name={p['name']!r}  pub={p['is_published']}  view={p.get('view_id')}\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  ERR: {e}\\\")\\n\\n# 2. Check ir.translation for the appointment type\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n[2] ir.translation for appointment.type\\\")\\ntry:\\n    t = models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \\\"ir.translation\\\", \\\"search_read\\\",\\n        [[[\\\"name\\\", \\\"=\\\", \\\"appointment.type,name\\\"], [\\\"res_id\\\", \\\"=\\\", 1]]],\\n        {\\\"fields\\\": [\\\"id\\\", \\\"lang\\\", \\\"value\\\", \\\"state\\\", \\\"type\\\"]})\\n    for tr in t:\\n        print(f\\\"  [{tr['id']:>3}] lang={tr['lang']}  state={tr['state']}  value={tr['value']!r}\\\")\\n    if not t:\\n        print(\\\"  (no translation overrides for appointment.type#1.name)\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  ERR: {e}\\\")\\n\\n# 3. Search ALL ir.translation rows that mention \\\"Discovery Consultation & More\\\"\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n[3] Any ir.translation rows with the old title text\\\")\\ntry:\\n    t = models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \\\"ir.translation\\\", \\\"search_read\\\",\\n        [[[\\\"value\\\", \\\"ilike\\\", \\\"Discovery Consultation & More\\\"]]],\\n        {\\\"fields\\\": [\\\"id\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"res_id\\\", \\\"lang\\\", \\\"value\\\", \\\"type\\\", \\\"state\\\"]})\\n    for tr in t:\\n        print(f\\\"  [{tr['id']:>3}] {tr['name']}  res_id={tr['res_id']}  lang={tr['lang']}  state={tr['state']}  value={tr['value']!r}\\\")\\n    if not t:\\n        print(\\\"  (none)\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  ERR: {e}\\\")\\n\\n# 4. Check the appointment.type #1 fully \\u2014 find ANY field still containing the old string\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n[4] appointment.type #1 \\u2014 every field, grep for the old title\\\")\\nappt = models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \\\"appointment.type\\\", \\\"read\\\", [[1]])[0]\\nhits = []\\nfor k, v in appt.items():\\n    if v is False or v is None: continue\\n    s = str(v)\\n    if \\\"Discovery Consultation & More\\\" in s or \\\"Discovery Consultation\\\" in s or \\\"Consultation & More\\\" in s:\\n        snippet = s if len(s) < 200 else s[:200]+\\\"...\\\"\\n        hits.append((k, snippet))\\nfor k, v in hits:\\n    print(f\\\"  {k:<35} = {v!r}\\\")\\nif not hits:\\n    print(\\\"  (no field on appointment.type contains the old text)\\\")\\n\\n# 5. Check view records linked to website pages\\nprint(\\\"\\\\n[5] ir.ui.view records that mention appointment or share\\\")\\ntry:\\n    views = models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \\\"ir.ui.view\\\", \\\"search_read\\\",\\n        [[[\\\"name\\\", \\\"ilike\\\", \\\"appointment\\\"], [\\\"type\\\", \\\"=\\\", \\\"qweb\\\"]]],\\n        {\\\"fields\\\": [\\\"id\\\", \\\"name\\\", \\\"key\\\", \\\"active\\\", \\\"inherit_id\\\", \\\"mode\\\"], \\\"limit\\\": 20})\\n    for v_ in views:\\n        print(f\\\"  [{v_['id']:>3}] {v_['key']:<55} active={v_['active']}\\\")\\nexcept Exception as e:\\n    print(f\\\"  ERR: {e}\\\")\\n\", \"filePath\": \"C:\\\\Users\\\\LLM-Test\\\\.mavis\\\\sessions\\\\mvs_8d6cdf45af11451ca152d51c37e4fa64\\\\workspace\\\\odoo_find_title.py\"}",
