      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have it:\n\n1. **No website.page for `/book/27e80afd`** — the share link uses a dynamic route, not a static page\n2. **ir.translation doesn't exist** — in Odoo 19, translations are stored differently\n3. **The appointment.type #1 fields are clean** — `name` is \"Discovery Consultation\", `display_name` is the same, no field contains the old text\n4. **The view `website_appointment.s_online_appointment` (id 3359)** is likely the one rendering the public appointment page\n\nSo where does the \"Discovery Consultation & More\" come from? The DB is clean. Let me look at the view's template code.\n\nWait — let me re-check. The page is rendered for the URL `/book/27e80afd`. This is a different route from `/appointment/discovery-consultation-1`. The `/book/<token>` route might be a \"shareable link\" feature that uses a different controller.\n\nLooking at the Odoo Appointment module source code:\n- The `/book/<token>` route is in `website_appointment/controllers/appointment.py`\n- The token is the `access_token` of the appointment.type OR a `share_token` of a specific booking\n\nWait, but I confirmed `access_token` doesn't exist on `appointment.type`. So where is the token `27e80afd` stored?\n\nLet me also re-check the appointment type — maybe the share token is on a related model.\n\nActually, I just realized something. Let me re-read the user's earlier message:\n\"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd \nmind u that this is ready so then if u can do your thing let me know what can be done... but then first and foremost fix the odoo site if thats active\"\n\nThe user said the link is \"ready\" and they can preview it. So the link works. The question is just how to make the page look like Calendly.\n\nNow, the H1 still says \"Discovery Consultation & More\" but the DB has \"Discovery Consultation\". This is a clear discrepancy. The only explanation is:\n- The page is using a DIFFERENT field, OR\n- The page is cached (but my cache-buster test showed it's not)\n\nWait, let me think... In Odoo 19, the appointment page might use a special field or the `display_name` of the appointment type, which could be different from `name`.\n\nActually, looking at the appointment.type data, the `display_name` is also \"Discovery Consultation\". So that's not it.\n\nHmm. Let me check if there's an `access_token` field somewhere else that ties to a different record. Maybe the share link `/book/27e80afd` is tied to a specific calendar event or a different appointment.\n\nLet me search for the token more broadly.\n\nActually wait — I notice from the search_read that the title shows \"&amp;\" which is HTML-escaped. The original text is \"Discovery Consultation & More\". My DB write was \"Discovery Consultation\" (no \"& More\"). The HTML escaping is correct.\n\nBut wait, looking at the Odoo source, in Odoo 19 the appointment page's title might come from the `name` field of the appointment type. If the DB has \"Discovery Consultation\" and the page shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\", then either:\n- The page is reading from a different record\n- There's some inheritance/override\n\nLet me check if there's an `appointment_online` or similar model that wraps the appointment type for the public page.\n\nActually, let me just look at the QWeb template `website_appointment.s_online_appointment` (id 3359) to see what it does. I can read the arch field.\n\nWait — I can also just try to read the view's arch to see the template. Let me do that.",
