      "type": "thought",
      "text": "NOW I see it clearly!\n\n**The share link `/book/27e80afd` is an `appointment.invite` (id 2)**, NOT directly an appointment type. The invite:\n- `short_code` = \"27e80afd\"\n- `access_token` = \"77a675dfa61549b2a3e91ad64fdd75b8\"\n- `book_url` = \"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd\"\n- `redirect_url` = \"/appointment/discovery-consultation-1?invite_token=77a675dfa61549b2a3e91ad64fdd75b8&filter_appointment_type_ids=%5B1%5D\"\n- `appointment_type_ids` = [1]\n- `staff_user_ids` = []  ← EMPTY! (this is why the host isn't shown)\n\nSo when someone clicks the share link `/book/27e80afd`, Odoo redirects to the appointment type page with invite params. The invite just sets a filter for the appointment type.\n\nThe OTHER invite (id 1) is the same:\n- `short_code` = \"539f5a8f\"\n- `book_url` = \"https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/539f5a8f\"\n- `staff_user_ids` = [2]  ← has the host\n\nThe user's share link has `staff_user_ids = []` — empty staff users. This might be why the page doesn't show the host info. Let me update this invite to include the host.\n\nAlso, the `redirect_url` includes `filter_staff_use...` (truncated) and `filter_appointment_type_ids=[1]`. The redirect uses `filter_appointment_type_ids=[1]` and probably `filter_staff_user_ids=[2]` to filter the page to show only the host's appointment.\n\nIf `staff_user_ids = []` on the invite, the page might not filter by host, so it shows all available slots.\n\nNow for the H1 issue:\n- The H1 on the public page comes from `appointment_type.name`\n- My change to `name` = \"Discovery Consultation\" should have updated it\n- But the H1 still shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\"\n\nWait, let me re-read the page HTML. The H1 was:\n```html\n<h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\">Discovery Consultation & More</h1>\n```\n\nIf this is rendered using `appointment_type.name`, and the name is now \"Discovery Consultation\", then this should show \"Discovery Consultation\". But it shows \"& More\".\n\nThis must be a cache. Let me bust the cache by writing to the appointment.type (bump write_date).\n\nActually, the redirect URL goes to `/appointment/discovery-consultation-1?invite_token=...&filter_appointment_type_ids=[1]`. The page rendered is the appointment type page. If Odoo caches the QWeb rendering per appointment type, writing to the appointment type should invalidate the cache.\n\nWait, I did write to it. Let me try writing again with a slight modification, then check.\n\nActually, maybe the issue is that the view is using a field that's not `name` but something else. Looking at the views, there's `website_appointment.website_calendar_index_topbar` with a generic H1 \"Choose your appointment\". But that's not the H1 I'm seeing.\n\nLet me look at the views that might render the appointment TYPE page. The H1 says \"Discovery Consultation & More\" — this is per-type, not a generic title. Let me find the view that renders it.\n\nLet me search views for the specific H1.",
      "timestamp": 1782263481844
    },
