 to clear caches is via the website's UI or via `clear_caches` on the env.\n\nLet me try:\n- `models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \"ir.ui.view\", \"read_template\", [[1117]])` — this should re-read the template\n- Or call the cron for cache invalidation\n\nActually, the simplest fix: just write to the view with a small change. Let me read the current arch, modify it slightly, and write it back. This forces a re-render.\n\nOr: try calling `clear_caches` via the `ir.qweb` model or via the `ir.ui.view` model with a specific signature.\n\nLet me try: `models.execute_kw(DB, uid, API_KEY, \"ir.ui.view\", \"write\", [[1117], {\"arch\": \"...\"}])` where arch is the same as current but with a tiny comment added.\n\nActually, the cleanest thing: there's a built-in Odoo method `clear_caches` on the registry, but it might not be exposed via XML-RPC. The website has a button to \"Clear Cache\" in the UI. Let me try to find the underlying method.\n\nLooking at Odoo's source:\n- `website.reset_template_cache()` is a thing\n- But it might not exist in 19.3\n\nLet me try other methods:\n- `ir.ui.view.clear_caches()` - this exists\n- But the call signature might be different\n\nLet me try with empty args:",
