      "type": "thought",
      "text": "Now I have a clear picture:\n\n**1. The appointment page intro IS rendering** (case-insensitive):\n- \"sovereign cloud journey\" ✓\n- \"video call\" pill ✓\n- \"30 minutes\" pill ✓\n- \"europe/london\" pill ✓\n- \"free\" pill ✓\n- H2 \"Discovery Consultation\" (from my intro HTML) ✓\n- \"Discovery Consultation & More\" still in title/H1 (cache)\n\nSo my customizations are 100% on the page. The intro is showing.\n\n**2. The host photo/name isn't shown** — the appointment page doesn't show the host (Andrea). The H1 doesn't show the host either. The `host: 'andrea'` marker is False. The host user is set (staff_user_ids=[2]) but the page doesn't render it. This might be because:\n- The host is shown conditionally (e.g., only for certain page templates)\n- The host section is in a different part of the page\n- The host info needs an image to be set\n\nThe Odoo Appointment page template might only show the host section if there's an `image_128` set on the host user. The user (uid=2) might not have an avatar set.\n\n**3. H1 is still \"Discovery Consultation & More\"** — this is a real cache issue. The H1 is from the view template `t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"`, and the DB has \"Discovery Consultation\". The H1 should update but it's stuck.\n\n**4. The backend /odoo (unauth) returns the login page** — that's correct, unauthenticated requests go to login. The actual SPA shell with the menu only appears when the user is logged in.\n\n**5. The home action wasn't set** — `action_discuss` (mail module) doesn't exist. The user's home_action_id remains false.\n\nSo what should I do now?\n\nFor the user's complaint (\"categorically wrong\"):\n- They were showing me the Odoo backend page with empty body\n- The body is empty because the SPA shell loads via JS, and view source shows empty\n- The actual rendered page (after JS) should have content\n\nIf the user is seeing a blank page in their browser, the JS is failing. The most likely cause:\n- The assets bundle was stale (I just deleted it, so it will recompile)\n- Some JS error\n\nNow that I deleted the assets, the next time the user hits /odoo in their browser, Odoo will recompile. The user needs to hard-refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R) to bypass browser cache.\n\nFor the H1 issue:\n- The DB has the right name\n- The view template uses `t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"`\n- The rendered page shows the old name\n- This is a QWeb view cache issue\n- To fix: invalidate the view's cache or wait for the next registry rebuild\n\nFor the home action:\n- `home_action_id` is false (default)\n- This is normal — Odoo shows the apps menu when no home action is set\n- The empty body might be because the apps menu is empty after the 9-module uninstall\n- Let me check what apps are still installed\n\nHmm, the user said \"categorically wrong\" about the Odoo site. Let me think about what they might be seeing:\n1. The Odoo backend (/odoo) - blank because the JS isn't running (assets issue - I just fixed)\n2. The Odoo appointment page (/book/27e80afd) - working with my customizations\n3. The H1 still shows old name - cache issue\n\nThe user pasted the HTML of the Odoo backend (the SPA shell with empty body). This is the source code view of /odoo. The user might have:\n- Done \"view source\" and seen empty body (misinterpreting)\n- Or seen a blank page in their browser\n\nEither way, the next refresh should help. The assets I deleted will be regenerated on next request.\n\nLet me wrap up with a clear message to the user:\n1. The Odoo backend is fixed (assets will recompile on refresh)\n2. They need to hard refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R)\n3. The appointment page is fully customized (intro, pills, etc.)\n4. The H1 cache issue remains - they'll need to invalidate manually or wait\n\nActually wait, let me also think about the \"categorically wrong\" claim more carefully. The user might be frustrated because:\n- The H1 is still wrong\n- The host isn't shown\n- The backend is blank\n\nI've addressed the backend (assets will recompile). The H1 is a cache issue I can't easily fix via API. The host is set in the DB but not rendering (might need an image).\n\nLet me also check: is there a way to invalidate the Odoo view cache for the public appointment page? I could:\n- Write to the view (bump write_date) - I tried this\n- Use a different method\n- Just have the user restart Odoo\n\nOr: maybe the H1 is cached in the user's BROWSER. A hard refresh (Ctrl+Shift+R) would bypass that.\n\nLet me give the user clear instructions:\n1. Hard refresh Ctrl+Shift+R on the Odoo pages\n2. The H1 should update to \"Discovery Consultation\" (the new name)\n3. The backend should render properly (assets recompile)\n4. If still issues, they may need to do it in Odoo UI\n\nLet me also mark all todos as done.\n\nActually, I want to do one more thing: try to invalidate the view cache by writing to the view in a way that the Odoo QWeb cache notices. The cache key includes the view's content. If I add/remove a space or change a comment, the content changes and the cache invalidates.\n\nBut wait — the view 1117's H1 uses `t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"`. The H1's rendered output depends on the `name` field of the record. The QWeb template itself doesn't change. The rendered output changes when the record changes.\n\nThe cache should invalidate on record change. But it's not. So the cache is keyed on the template, not the record value.\n\nHmm. This is a real puzzle. Let me try one more thing: write to the view with a different content.\n\nActually, you know what — let me just try a completely different approach. Let me write to view 1117 with a different value for the H1 to see if the page picks it up. If the page picks up my new H1 text, then the cache is being read on each request and just the record value isn't being used. If the page doesn't pick up my new H1, then the cache is truly stale.\n\nWait, I can also check by looking at the page response. If the H1 shows \"Discovery Consultation\" (from a recent write) but the page title still shows \"Discovery Consultation & More\", that tells me something.\n\nOK let me just wrap up. The H1 cache issue is something the user can address via Odoo's UI (clear cache button, restart, or just wait). My main fixes (tour error, appointment customization, assets bundle) are all done.\n\nLet me give the user a clear summary and tell them to:\n1. Hard refresh the Odoo backend (Ctrl+Shift+R)\n2. Hard refresh the appointment page\n3. The assets will recompile on next request\n\nThe H1 will eventually catch up. If they need it immediately, they can use Odoo's \"Clear Cache\" from the website editor.\n\nLet me also note: I could try writing a tiny no-op to view 1117 again with a slightly different approach. But I've already done that and it didn't help.\n\nActually, let me try ONE more thing: write the view with a different name (e.g., add a space at the end of the H1 text, or change the t-out to t-field). If the view's content changes, the QWeb cache should invalidate.\n\nWait, `t-out` vs `t-field`:\n- `t-out` is for static text output\n- `t-field` is for editable field rendering (used in form views)\n\nIf I change `t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"` to `t-field=\"appointment_type.name\"`, the H1 would be editable in dev mode. But the rendered output should be the same.\n\nBut changing the QWeb syntax might cause issues. Let me not do that.\n\nThe simplest hack: add a comment to the H1 line in the view. The view content changes, the cache invalidates, the next request renders the new H1.\n\nBut I already added a comment (line `<!--bust-->`) and it didn't help. So either:\n- The comment didn't get added to the view (the write didn't go through)\n- The cache is more aggressive than just the view content\n- The page is being served from a different source\n\nLet me check the view 1117 to see if my comment is there.",
