      "text": "H1 still showing old name. The cache is really stuck. Let me think about why.\n\nLooking at the H1 source: `<h1 class=\"d-none d-md-block mb-4 h4\" t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"/>`. The `t-out` is a T-field expression that gets the value of `appointment_type.name` at render time.\n\nThe DB has `name = 'Discovery Consultation'`. So at render time, the H1 should be \"Discovery Consultation\".\n\nBut the rendered H1 is \"Discovery Consultation & More\". This means EITHER:\n1. The render is using a CACHED version of the rendered H1 (not re-rendering)\n2. The render is using a STALE value of `appointment_type.name`\n\nFor option 1: I added a comment to the view to invalidate the QWeb template cache. The view's write_date changed. But the H1 is still old.\n\nFor option 2: This is unlikely because Odoo's ORM cache is per-record and the record has the new name.\n\nThere's also option 3: The public page is served from a CDN or cache layer that doesn't see the view change.\n\nOr option 4: The Odoo public website has a separate cache for public pages that's keyed differently.\n\nAt this point, I've tried everything I can via the XML-RPC API. The cache is REALLY stuck. The user might need to:\n- Do a server-side cache clear (via Odoo UI)\n- Or restart the Odoo workers\n\nBut wait — the user can do this themselves. Let me give them clear instructions.\n\nActually, let me also think about what to tell the user. They're frustrated. They want a job well done. I should:\n1. Tell them what's been done\n2. Tell them what they need to do\n3. Be clear about what's still broken\n\nStatus:\n- ✅ Tour error fixed\n- ✅ Appointment page customized (intro, pills, 30 min, etc.)\n- ✅ Share link works\n- ✅ Canonical URL works\n- ✅ Backend assets cache cleared (will recompile on next user request)\n- ✅ Home action NOT set (can't find a good one — discuss action doesn't exist)\n- ❌ H1 cache STILL stuck at \"Discovery Consultation & More\"\n\nThe H1 cache issue is the only remaining