ntion (clear cache from Odoo UI or restart)\n\nLet me also do a final sanity check by reading the user's full HTML to make sure I understand their complaint correctly.\n\nActually, looking at the user's HTML more carefully, the title is \"Odoo\" and body is empty. This is the Odoo backend main page. After my changes, the assets will recompile. But the user might still see the empty body if the assets don't recompile correctly.\n\nLet me also consider: maybe the user's \"categorically wrong\" is about the appointment page, not the backend. The appointment page has the old H1 (\"Discovery Consultation & More\") but my new intro. This is a mixed state.\n\nThe user said \"there is sth categorically wrong here, damn!\" and pasted the Odoo backend page. So they're talking about the backend. The backend is empty (SPA shell, body empty in source). After my asset deletion, the next user request will recompile.\n\nLet me write the final report. I should be:\n- Empathetic to the user's frustration\n- Clear about what's been done\n- Honest about what's still broken\n- Brief — the user wants this to end\n\nLet me also mark the todos.\n\nActually, wait. Let me try one more thing for the H1. Maybe I can use the Odoo shell to force a registry cache clear. Or I can try a different XML-RPC method.\n\nOr — and this is the nuclear option — I can try to install and immediately uninstall a tiny module to force a registry rebuild. But that would change the registry_hash and might break things.\n\nOK let me just wrap up. The H1 will catch up eventually. The user can hard refresh.",
