      "text": "Honest answer: I fixed the parts I could reach via the API. There's one thing I couldn't crack, and that's the \"categorically wrong\" you can see in the browser.\n\n**What I did**\n- ✅ TourService error — gone (`tour_enabled: false`, `current_tour: null`)\n- ✅ Appointment type #1 — name \"Discovery Consultation\", 30 min, host = Andrea, auto-confirm on, intro HTML with pills, confirmation HTML, published\n- ✅ Share invite #2 — host filter fixed so slots show only Andrea's calendar\n- ✅ Backend assets bundle cache deleted (the 5 stale `ir.attachment` rows from right after the module uninstall). Odoo will recompile on the next request when you hit `/odoo` in your browser.\n- ✅ Public appointment page (`/book/27e80afd`) — all 7 intro markers confirmed live: \"sovereign cloud journey\", \"video call\" pill, \"30 minutes\" pill, \"europe/london\" pill, \"free\" pill, H2 \"Discovery Consultation\", no tour markers in HTML\n\n**What I couldn't fix (and it's the one you're seeing)**\n- ❌ The H1 / `<title>` on the appointment page still reads \"Discovery Consultation & More\" even though `appointment.type#1.name = \"Discovery Consultation\"` in the DB and view 1117 is `<h1 t-out=\"appointment_type.name\"/>`. I tried three cache-bust approaches (re-write the record, re-write view 1117 with a comment, change the t-out attribute) — nothing shifted the rendered output. The Odoo public-page QWeb cache is keyed on something I can't reach from XML-RPC, and the registry hash hasn't changed either (`d99bd19c…` is the same as it was 5 hours ago).\n- ❌ \"View source\" on `/odoo` showing empty `<body>` is normal for an Odoo SPA — that page fills in via JS after load. But the *rendered* page may also be blank right now if the assets recompile didn't complete. **Please hard-refresh in your browser: `Ctrl + Shift + R` on the `/odoo` page.** That should force the recompile and either fix it or show the actual JS error.\n\n**To actually unstick the H1 (one of these will do it — I can't do any of them via the API)**\n1. **Quickest** — in Odoo: open the website editor on the appointment page → top-right \"...\" menu → \"Clear Cache\". Two clicks.\n2. **If you have shell access** — `odoo-bin shell -d andiekobbie -u website_appointment --stop-after-init` will force a registry rebuild that invalidates everything.\n3. **Nuclear** — bounce the Odoo workers (Settings → Server restart, or just `systemctl restart odoo`).\n\nI know you've been patient through a lot of rounds here, and the H1 is the visible proof that the job isn't fully done. I can't punch through that last layer from where I'm sitting — the Odoo public website cache is genuinely server-side. If you hit the editor's \"Clear Cache\" and the H1 still doesn't update, tell me what you see and I'll find another angle.",
