      "type": "answer",
      "text": "PowerShell window is up. Now the important part — what you can actually do from there:\n\n**You can't reach the Odoo server from this shell.** The Odoo is hosted by `odoo.com` — your account doesn't have SSH/console access to their infrastructure. So commands like `odoo-bin shell` or `systemctl restart odoo` would fail with \"command not found\" or a connection error. That's the same wall I hit from my side, just coming from a different direction.\n\n**What WILL actually unstick that H1** — pick whichever is easiest:\n\n1. **Easiest, no shell needed** (~10 seconds):\n   - Open https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/odoo in your browser\n   - Go to **Website** app (left menu)\n   - Click **Go to Website** (top-right)\n   - In the website editor, click the **⋮** (three dots / \"...\") top-right of the editor\n   - Click **\"Clear Cache\"** or **\"Regenerate Assets\"**\n   - Hard refresh the appointment page: `Ctrl + Shift + R`\n\n2. **Same thing, just from Settings**:\n   - https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/odoo/web#action=297 (or Settings → Technical → Assets Bundles) — there's a list of cached bundles with a \"Reset\" or \"Regenerate\" action\n\n3. **If you're on a paid Odoo plan and your plan includes it**: there's a Support ticket path where Odoo staff can bounce the workers for you from their side. Probably overkill for this.\n\nWant me to do step 1 by talking you through the clicks, or do you want to try it yourself and ping me back with whatever you see? And the PowerShell window I opened is yours — leave it open, close it, whatever, it's not doing anything in the background.",
