      "text": "Sorry — that was a sloppy \"it\". Two things you might mean by that:\n\n**1. The PowerShell window I just opened** — it's a text command line for *your* PC. It can launch apps, move files, run scripts, install software, etc. But for the Odoo problem, it can't help because the Odoo lives on `odoo.com`'s servers, not on your machine. You can close that window — no harm done by leaving it open either.\n\n**2. The actual fix I keep mentioning — the \"Clear Cache\" thing in Odoo's website editor** — that's a button inside the Odoo web app, not on your PC. Two clicks. Want me to walk you through the exact clicks, screen by screen?\n\nIf yes, the path is:\n\n1. In your browser, go to **https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/odoo**\n2. Hard refresh the page once (**Ctrl + Shift + R**)\n3. Look at the **left sidebar menu** — find the app called **\"Website\"** (it'll have a little globe icon). Click it.\n4. That'll open the website editor. Top-right of the editor you'll see either a **⋮** (three dots) or an **\"Edit\"** toggle. Click into edit mode.\n5. Once you're in edit mode, look again top-right — there should be a **\"...\"** menu or a **\"Settings\"** sidebar. In there, find **\"Clear Cache\"** or **\"Assets: Regenerate\"** and click it.\n6. The editor will reload. **Hard refresh the appointment page** (`Ctrl + Shift + R` on `https://andiekobbie.odoo.com/book/27e80afd`).\n7. The H1 should now read **\"Discovery Consultation\"** instead of \"Discovery Consultation & More\".\n\nTell me where you get stuck (or \"done, it works\" / \"done, still broken\") and I'll go from there. And if any of those buttons isn't where I said, screenshot it and I'll look.",
